ExpertWall: A Platform for Connecting Engineering Experts and Users Seeking Expertise

ExpertWall is a web application that connects skilled engineers with users seeking assistance with technical issues. The platform facilitates seamless knowledge exchange and problem-solving, empowering developers to collaborate effectively.

Key Features

User Registration: Users create profiles with their name, email, phone number, and question or help request details.
Expert Registration: Experts provide detailed profiles with their name, email, phone number, educational background, work experience, and availability schedule.
Secure Payment Transactions: Stripe powers secure and reliable payment processing for expert services.
React Stack: React, React Router DOM, React Spinner, React Icon, and Framer Motion are combined to create a powerful frontend experience.
Tailwind CSS: Provides a structured and visually appealing layout for the application.
Cloudinary: Images are stored and managed using Cloudinary's secure and scalable infrastructure.

Benefits of Using ExpertWall

Effortless Knowledge Exchange: Experts share their expertise with users, bridging the gap between knowledge and problem-solving.
Collaborative Problem-Solving: Users and experts work together to resolve technical issues, accelerating development and innovation.
Enhanced Developer Productivity: Experts provide quick and efficient assistance, freeing up developers' time to focus on core tasks.

How to Install and Run ExpertWall Locally

Clone the Repository:
Clone the repository from GitHub to your local machine using the following command:

open the folder in any code editor, go to the terminal

git clone https://github.com/frankkode/experts-wall-app.git


Install Dependencies:
Navigate to the backend and frontend folders separately and install the required dependencies using the following commands:

in your terminal (root folder):
cd backend
npm install

in terminal (root folder)
cd frontend
npm install

Environmental Setup:
Create .env files in the backend and add the following environment variables:

backend/.env

PORT=5005
MONGO_URI=YOUR_MONGODB_URI
JWT_SECRET_KEY=YOUR_JWT_SECRET_KEY
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=YOUR_STRIPE_SECRET_KEY
CLIENT_SITE_URL=http://localhost:5173

Replace YOUR_MONGODB_URI, YOUR_JWT_SECRET_KEY, and YOUR_STRIPE_SECRET_KEY with your actual values.

Running the Backend:
Navigate to the backend folder and run the following command to start the backend server:

terminal:
npm run start-dev

Running the Frontend:
Navigate to the frontend folder and run the following command to start the frontend application:

terminal
npm run dev

Accessing the Application:
Open your web browser and go to http://localhost:5173 (or any other port you specified on your env file) to access the ExpertWall application.

Testing:
To run the test suite, navigate to the frontend folder and run the following command:

terminal
npm test (remember to change type from "type"="module" to "type"="commonjs" in your frontend -> package.json file)

